Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.30,0:00:06.79,Caption,,0,0,0,,A user starts in LexNordic, a private Swedish migration consultation workspace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.00,0:00:10.42,Caption,,0,0,0,,The workspace uses Supabase Auth, so sessions, chat history, matters, and files stay user-owned.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.62,0:00:12.71,Caption,,0,0,0,,The user asks a normal migration question. They do not need to know the legal route first.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.91,0:00:21.21,Caption,,0,0,0,,The answer streams while route, documents, sources, risks, and packet readiness are checked.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.41,0:00:32.28,Caption,,0,0,0,,The default answer stays simple, but the proof layer reveals the Band-style specialist work trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.48,0:00:40.89,Caption,,0,0,0,,The same conversation becomes a structured matter with route, evidence, source, and packet state.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.09,0:00:48.61,Caption,,0,0,0,,The Route page compares permit paths, readiness, next questions, and current rule overlays.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.81,0:00:56.27,Caption,,0,0,0,,Evidence requirements become actionable document tasks instead of scattered checklist notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.47,0:01:12.91,Caption,,0,0,0,,Band collaboration is shown directly: pixel agents pass a shared case baton through the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.11,0:01:26.77,Caption,,0,0,0,,The output is an AI case packet: checklist, next actions, source trail, and no automatic authority filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.97,0:01:34.97,Caption,,0,0,0,,LexNordic turns migration uncertainty into a source-grounded, multi-agent consultation workflow.
